              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">p181 The great mathematician Chu Shih-chiehć&oelig;ąä¸&ndash;ć?°, trained in the northern school, migrated south to Yang-chou, where his books were printed but he could find no disciples. In consequence, the more sophisticated of his achievements became incomprehensible to following generations. But the basic scientific texts at least were common property everywhere.

p194 By Ming times, there was no one left ...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2013-05-20 09:28</span>
                  
                </p>
